HEADWORD: Heterodoxy
<hw>Het"er*o*dox`y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/: cf.
F. <ets>h⟦eacute⟧t⟦eacute⟧rodoxie</ets>.]</ety> <def>An opinion or
doctrine, or a system of doctrines, contrary to some established
standard of faith, as the Scriptures, the creed or standards of a
church, etc.; heresy.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Bull.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
